<title type="html"><![CDATA[Vertical Parallax effect in Battletoads]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8364&amp;p=86964#p86964"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">Shiru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />You don't need a scanline counter, only CHR RAM.<br /></div><br />Just wanted to note that you can do the same trick with CHR-ROM, if the mapper can swap small enough chunks. It's actually *easier* with CHR-ROM because you don't waste time rotating graphics and uploading them to VRAM, you just switch the appropriate bank every frame and you're done. The only disadvantage is that it wastes a significant amount of CHR-ROM, because all possible rotations must be present. Most games in the videos I showed use CHR-ROM, not RAM.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Wed Nov 30, 2011 5:12 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
